&lt;h2&gt;Patient Pathway Co-Ordinator&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band 3:£20,771 - £22,199 per annum, incl HCAS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Patient Pathway Co-ordinator for SABR &amp; Private Patients&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: Guildford based with occasional rotations at Redhill, Surrey&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants are invited to apply for the role of Patient Pathway Coordinator. The post holder will provide support across a range of administrative functions including the Stereotactic and Private Service within oncology.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;They will ensure the complex pathways are correctly managed, and that all relevant patient data is collected and collated, according to the department’s needs. The post holder will require excellent communication and organisational skills. They will be expected to liaise directly with patients and carers, as well as a number of different professions, both within and external to the trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Having achieved Foundation Trust status and been identified as a CHKS 40 Top Hospital and a Top 100 Healthcare employer, our focus is to offer the best possible care and treatment outcomes for our patients, and to continue to be the employer of choice for our staff. We focus on giving our patients the best outcomes of care and an excellent experience whilst in our hospital. By ensuring a skilled and motivated staff group, we aim to best meet patients’ needs and ensure excellent productivity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We serve a population of 1.3 million cancer patients, with the main Radiotherapy Centre on the host site in Guildford, and a satellite centre at the East Surrey Hospital, Redhill Surrey.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The radiotherapy team is a close knit team that welcomes enthusiastic individuals seeking a new opportunity.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;For additional information or to organise an informal visit, please call Julie Hanson, Radiotherapy Administration Manager at the Royal Surrey County Hospital on 01483 571122 Ext 2103.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Closing Date: 17/11/2020&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
